SECTION 1: THE INTEGER INVENTORY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Every integer below is extracted from phys24_lib beta
  coefficients. No cosmological input. Pure Level 1.

  FROM b2_SM = -19/6:
      |numerator| = 19 (dimensionless)     19.0

  FROM b2_mod = -13/6:
      |numerator| = 13 (dimensionless)     13.0

  FROM b3_mod = -20/3:
      |numerator| = 20 (dimensionless)     20.0

  FROM b1_SM = 41/10:
      |numerator| = 41 (dimensionless)     41.0

  YANG-MILLS INTEGER:
      11 (dimensionless)                   11.0

  DERIVED INTEGERS:
      N_gen = 3 (dimensionless)            3.0
      3 * 19 = 57 (dimensionless)          57.0
      3 * 13 = 39 (dimensionless)          39.0
      2 * 11 = 22 (dimensionless)          22.0
      Asymmetry db2/db1 = 15 (dimensionless) 15.0
      Pure-gauge gap = 2 (dimensionless)   2.0

SECTION 2: THE FORMULA FRAMEWORK
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  All formulas use ONLY:
    alpha_em (from library, Level 2)
    beta integers (from library, Level 1)
    R2, R4, pi (from library, Level 1)
  No cosmological constants as input.

  alpha_em (dimensionless)                 0.0072973525643
  VP step = 1/(12*R2) = 1/(3*pi) (dimensionless) 0.10610329539
  base = alpha/(3*pi) (dimensionless)      0.00077427315473

SECTION 3: FORMULA 1 — COSMOLOGICAL CONSTANT SCALE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Formula: log10(Lambda_Pl) = N_gen * |b2_num| * log10(coupling)

  Version A (SM, bare alpha):
      exponent = 3 * 19 = 57 (dimensionless) 57.0
      prediction: log10(Lambda) (dimensionless) -121.79957623
      measured: log10(Lambda) (dimensionless) -121.54
      miss (decades) (dimensionless)       0.25957623187

  Version B (VL, alpha/(3*pi)):
      exponent = 3 * 13 = 39 (dimensionless) 39.0
      prediction: log10(Lambda) (dimensionless) -121.33312613
      measured: log10(Lambda) (dimensionless) -121.54
      miss (decades) (dimensionless)       0.20687387222

  NOTE: Version A overshoots by -0.26, Version B undershoots by 0.21
  The measured value sits BETWEEN the SM and VL predictions.

    Interpolation fraction f (dimensionless) 0.44350696978
  (f=1 is pure SM, f=0 is pure VL)

SECTION 4: FORMULA 2 — DARK MATTER RATIO
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Formula: DM/baryon = (2 * 11 / |b2_mod_num|) * pi
         = (2 * YM / 13) * pi
         = (22/13) * pi

