SECTION 10: VP STEP FORMULA — INTERNAL CONSISTENCY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Formula A: (1-r) = alpha/(3*pi)
      = 0.00077427315473 (dimensionless)   0.00077427315473

  Formula B: (1-r) = alpha^2 * pi^2 * 20/13
      = 0.0008085689265 (dimensionless)    0.0008085689265

    ratio B/A (dimensionless)              1.0442941507

    = alpha * 60*pi^3/13 (dimensionless)   1.0442941507
  The two formulas differ by alpha * 60*pi^3/13 ~ 1.044
  This is close to 1 (ratio = 1.04429), meaning both formulas
  predict nearly the same (1-r) despite different structure.

  Target (1-r) at N=100 from H0 data:
      (1-r) target (dimensionless)         0.00080923105932
      miss A (percent)                     4.3198916043
      miss B (percent)                     0.081822467652

